article.headline: Norfolk St. 96, Florida A&amp,M 69
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Michael Deloach scored 28 points to pace Norfolk State to a 96-69 victory over Florida A&M on Monday night. Deloach shot 12-for-18 and added six rebounds for the Spartans (8-13, 6-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Aleek Pauline chipped in with 16 points. Norfolk State went on a 12-1 run early in the first half, taking a 20-8 lead after a pair of free throws from Kevin Worsley with 11:51 remaining. They would go to hold a commanding 50-25 lead at halftime, thanks to a 13-3 run to end the half. Florida A&M (6-16, 4-6) was paced by Larry Jackson, who scored 18 points and grabbed six rebounds. Lamar Twitty contributed with 16 points and 11 rebounds. The Spartans shot 51.5 percent from the field (35-for-68) and 40 percent from 3-point range (10-for-25). The Rattlers shot only 59.3 percent from the free-throw line (16-for-27).
